                            <comment id="12797558" author="larsgeorge" created="Thu, 7 Jan 2010 08:38:46 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hey Bassam,&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I did the BASE64 encoding back then because of the same reason you are facing now, i.e. the scan has so many options and subclasses that the easiest was to encode it as a serialized object and recreate it on the other end. I thought about a similar set of options but when arriving at the filters I stopped and went the different route. But as long as yours is an alternative to the fully specified Scan then all well.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Lars&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
